A Decision Tree is a supervised machine learning algorithm used for both classification and regression tasks.
It works by splitting the data into branches based on feature values until the model reaches a final decision (leaf node).

A decision tree resembles a flowchart:

Root → Decision Nodes → Leaf Nodes



from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.datasets import load_iris

# Load dataset
data = load_iris()
X = data.data
y = data.target

# Create model
model = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='gini')
model.fit(X, y)

print("Predicted:", model.predict([[5.1, 3.5, 1.4, 0.2]]))




from sklearn import tree
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
tree.plot_tree(model, filled=True)
plt.show()

 Predicted: [0]

